There could be one or multiple reasons for blocked request. 
Listing down the possible reasons:

1. Cross-Origin Resource sharing(CORS) restriction 
The server interview.com might be returning different or invalid domains than expected, or it may be missing.
expected Header - Access-Control-Allow-Origin: https://hiring.com

2. Server should return proper acces control headers
Expected returns for different headers:
Access-Control-Allow-Methods: POST, GET, OPTIONS etc.
Access-Control-Allow-Headers: Authorization, Content-Type etc.
If its missing in the request might get blocked.

3.If there are Mixed contents(HTTP and HTTPS) browser might block the requests.

4.Security systems like: Cloudflare or AWS WAF, Firewall might block unusual traffic or non-browser requests,

5. Missing Authentication token can one of the reason.
If interview.com expects API Key or Token or JWT or Session cookie and itâ€™s not sent or invalid, request might fail.
